{"word":"H1310 - בָּשַׁל - bâshal - baw-shal' - Bake","slug":"H1310","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בָּשַׁל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>bâshal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>baw-shal'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bake"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05DC; - ba&#x0302;shal</b> - <i>baw-shal'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>boil</i> up; hence to <i>be done</i> in cooking; figuratively to <i>ripen: - </i>bake, boil, bring forth, is ripe, roast, seethe, sod (be sodden)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1311\">H1311</a>, <a href=\"#/H1312\">H1312</a>, <a href=\"#/H4018\">H4018</a>"}]}